3a - Line 5 creates a new array called list and assigns it to a variable "list".

3b - Line 8 calls the add_task method and creates new task called "Feed the cat".

3c - Line 14 prints the second task from list to the terminal.

3d - Line 31 calls the "complete!" method from task and marks it as complete.

4a - I think the advantage to OOP is that by using classes you have more flexibility to handle a variety of unique scenarios.

4b - I think the advantage to procedural is having your code all in one place without having to cross reference multiple files.